DOCKER CLI COMMANDS WITH REDIS — SHORT & CLEAN STEPS
 Step 1: Pull Redis Image
 Command: docker pull redis
 Step 2: Run Redis Container
 Command: docker run --name my-redis -d redis
 • Creates & starts container.
 • -d runs in background.
 Step 3: Check Running Containers
 Command: docker ps
 Step 4: Access Redis
 Command: docker exec -it my-redis redis-cli
 Example Redis Commands:
 SET name "Alice"
 GET name
 exit
 Step 5: Stop Container
 Command: docker stop my-redis
 Step 6: Restart Container
 Command: docker start my-redis
 Step 7: Remove Redis Container
 Command: docker rm my-redis
 Step 8: Remove Redis Image
 Command: docker rmi redis
 WORKING WITH DOCKERFILE
 Step 1: Setup Folder
 Windows: Create C:\DockerProjects\Redis
 Mac/Linux: mkdir ~/DockerProjects/Redis
 Step 2: Create Dockerfile
 Content:
 FROM redis:latest
CMD ["redis-server"]
 DOCKER COMMANDS
 1. docker build -t redisnew .
 • Builds image.
 2. docker run --name myredisnew -d redisnew
 3. docker ps
 4. docker stop myredisnew
 5. docker login
 6. docker ps -a
 7. docker commit 0e993d2009a1 budarajumadhurika/redis1
 8. docker images
 9. docker push budarajumadhurika/redis1
 10. docker rm 0e993d2009a1
 11. docker rmi budarajumadhurika/redis1
 12. docker ps -a
 13. docker logout
 14. docker pull budarajumadhurika/redis1
 15. docker run --name myredis -d budarajumadhurika/redis1
 16. docker exec -it myredis redis-cli
 17. SET name "Abcdef"
 18. GET name
19. exit
 20. docker ps -a
 21. docker stop myredis
 22. docker rm 50a6e4a9c326
 23. docker images
 24. docker rmi budarajumadhurika/redis1
 Step 3: Logout
 Command: docker logout
